And you brought your --
your little buds.

252
00:14:36.778 --> 00:14:38.178
Ted?
Stand down.

253
00:14:38.212 --> 00:14:40.347
They didn't ask for this.
You can say that again.

254
00:14:40.381 --> 00:14:42.149
Somebody better get
the disposal running.

255
00:14:42.182 --> 00:14:43.618
There's fishbones
in there.

256
00:14:43.651 --> 00:14:46.286
It's called
a garbage disposal!

257
00:14:46.320 --> 00:14:49.758
That was your voice
on my leg phone.

258
00:14:49.791 --> 00:14:50.924
You're his friend?

259
00:14:50.958 --> 00:14:54.328
Kind of.
I'm your grandson.

260
00:14:54.361 --> 00:14:57.766
Well. it looks like we're
gonna be here for a while. huh?

261
00:14:57.799 --> 00:14:59.199
Where's that fucking
red button?

262
00:14:59.233 --> 00:15:04.506
Uh. hey. uh. me?
H-Hologram guy?

263
00:15:04.539 --> 00:15:06.674
- Garage?
<i>- Yes?</i>

264
00:15:06.708 --> 00:15:08.041
Y-You can hear me.

265
00:15:08.075 --> 00:15:10.411
Uh. where's this guy
keep his tools?

266
00:15:12.781 --> 00:15:13.914
Holy shit.

267
00:15:13.947 --> 00:15:15.215
Hey. Teddy.

268
00:15:15.249 --> 00:15:18.586
As long as you're building
spaceman stuff...

269
00:15:25.959 --> 00:15:27.662
Yeah. Alright!

270
00:15:27.695 --> 00:15:29.229
I'm gonna get
another drink.

271
00:15:29.263 --> 00:15:31.965
Come on. Ted. We were
beating you before this. too.

272
00:15:31.999 --> 00:15:33.333
Gimme another pitcher.
Sure.

273
00:15:33.367 --> 00:15:35.068
Are you one of those hicks
with robot arms?

274
00:15:35.102 --> 00:15:36.270
What'd you call me?

275
00:15:36.303 --> 00:15:38.071
I thought you guys
were owning it.

276
00:15:38.105 --> 00:15:39.908
I'll make it interesting.
Teddy.

277
00:15:45.279 --> 00:15:49.884
Tough luck!
That's a hard spare to hit.

278
00:15:49.918 --> 00:15:52.986
Guys. I'm gonna
have to ask you to leave.

279
00:15:54.254 --> 00:15:55.757
What are you doing out here?

280
00:15:55.790 --> 00:15:57.958
Beth made pancakes.
I'm busy.

281
00:15:57.991 --> 00:15:59.193
You're wearing
his clothes now.

282
00:15:59.226 --> 00:16:00.829
It has pockets.
it's not a symbol.

283
00:16:00.862 --> 00:16:02.897
Teddy. you know
what would be cool?

284
00:16:02.931 --> 00:16:05.232
If I had laser eyes.

285
00:16:05.265 --> 00:16:08.001
Or. okay. one eye is a laser.

286
00:16:08.035 --> 00:16:09.737
and the other sees
through clothes.

287
00:16:10.638 --> 00:16:12.272
What the hell
is that?!

288
00:16:12.306 --> 00:16:14.975
Just go in.

289
00:16:15.008 --> 00:16:17.978
I can see our bowling alley.
We're going home.

290
00:16:18.011 --> 00:16:21.114
So. we won?
We -- We beat this guy?
Sure.

291
00:16:21.148 --> 00:16:22.382
-Yeah!
-Booyah!

292
00:16:22.416 --> 00:16:24.051
-We did it!
-We're goin' home. boys!

293
00:16:24.084 --> 00:16:25.587
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

294
00:16:25.620 --> 00:16:27.154
And. uh. you'll gimme lasers

295
00:16:27.187 --> 00:16:28.723
when we. uh. get back home?

296
00:16:28.756 --> 00:16:29.891
Oh!

297
00:16:29.924 --> 00:16:32.660
Hey. want me to keep an eye
on your old stuff?

298
00:16:32.694 --> 00:16:36.396
Sell it if you want.
Buy Luisa something nice.

299
00:16:42.637 --> 00:16:44.404
He looks pretty normal to me.

300
00:16:44.438 --> 00:16:46.106
Talk to him. then.

301
00:16:46.139 --> 00:16:48.342
Dad? Oh. God! Ugh!

302
00:16:48.375 --> 00:16:50.344
He's still Ted. apparently.

303
00:16:50.377 --> 00:16:52.714
There's a difference?

304
00:16:59.086 --> 00:17:00.420
You see what I'm saying?

305
00:17:00.454 --> 00:17:02.456
I'm not staying
if I can't swim.

306
00:17:10.965 --> 00:17:16.771
♪ Sometimes I don't know where
this dirty road is taking me ♪

307
00:17:18.338 --> 00:17:23.443
♪ Sometimes I don't even know
the reason why ♪

308
00:17:23.477 --> 00:17:26.046
♪ But I guess
I keep a-gamblin' ♪

309
00:17:26.079 --> 00:17:29.517
♪ Lots of booze
and lots of ramblin' ♪

310
00:17:31.351 --> 00:17:36.223
♪ Well. it's easier than just
awaiting 'round to die ♪

311
00:18:02.149 --> 00:18:03.618
Well.
look who's back.

312
00:18:03.651 --> 00:18:06.253
Came to pour one
out for Marjorie.

313
00:18:06.286 --> 00:18:08.155
Marjorie's over there.

314
00:18:08.188 --> 00:18:09.991
<i>This</i> is Little Mike.

315
00:18:10.024 --> 00:18:11.291
Oh. Jesus.

316
00:18:11.325 --> 00:18:13.226
He got run through
on his own robot arm.

317
00:18:13.260 --> 00:18:14.896
My boy!
Fuck.

318
00:18:14.929 --> 00:18:15.997
He was drunk.

319
00:18:16.030 --> 00:18:17.632
Guess he had
something in his eye.

320
00:18:17.665 --> 00:18:19.601
I didn't mean for any of this
to happen. you guys.

321
00:18:19.634 --> 00:18:23.071
It was just nice
to vacation with dumb people.

322
00:18:23.103 --> 00:18:24.505
You did this.

323
00:18:24.539 --> 00:18:27.675
you fake outsider
piece of shit.

324
00:18:42.155 --> 00:18:43.958
Morty.
 We're in the middle of a game.

325
00:18:43.992 --> 00:18:47.061
M-M-Morty. G--
Grandpa needs you.

326
00:18:47.095 --> 00:18:48.796
G-Grandpa needs you. Morty.

327
00:18:48.830 --> 00:18:51.164
C-Come on it'll just take a minute.
 Uh. okay Rick.

328
00:18:51.198 --> 00:18:52.834
I mean. Ted.
What are we --

329
00:18:52.867 --> 00:18:54.167
What are we
calling him now?

330
00:18:54.201 --> 00:18:56.004
Jesus!
That's really dangerous!

331
00:18:56.037 --> 00:18:57.739
It's empty.
I-I don't know how to --

332
00:18:57.772 --> 00:19:00.508
How do we get more. Morty?
We gotta get more.

333
00:19:00.541 --> 00:19:02.810
Oh. great. the one time
I was winning.

334
00:19:02.844 --> 00:19:04.177
Can you take your grandfather

335
00:19:04.211 --> 00:19:05.546
back out to the garage.
please. Morty?

336
00:19:05.580 --> 00:19:07.548
That is a troubling
family dynamic.

337
00:19:07.582 --> 00:19:09.282
Everybody knows that.
right?

338
00:19:09.316 --> 00:19:11.184
We can discuss it
after we get this thing...
Ow! Ow!

339
00:19:11.218 --> 00:19:12.419
...off your father.

340
00:19:12.452 --> 00:19:14.287
Kn-Know what --
know what. Morty?

341
00:19:14.321 --> 00:19:16.323
I'm not going back there ever.

342
00:19:16.356 --> 00:19:18.291
Oh!
Stupid bowling.

343
00:19:18.325 --> 00:19:21.361
Bottle-shooting morons.
Idiot trophy.

344
00:19:21.395 --> 00:19:23.898
Aw. w-wait. no. you don't wanna
keep some of these?

345
00:19:23.931 --> 00:19:25.399
Y-You look so happy.

346
00:19:25.432 --> 00:19:27.334
Aaaaahhh! Don't -- Don't --
Don't shred me. Rick!

347
00:19:27.367 --> 00:19:30.538
It's trash now. Morty!
Drop it!
Ooh! Ahh! Ohh!

348
00:19:32.406 --> 00:19:34.709
I'm sorry I tried
to shred you. Morty.

349
00:19:34.742 --> 00:19:38.412
Y-Y-You're a nice kid.
a good -- good boy.

350
00:19:38.445 --> 00:19:40.048
You should have your grandpa.

351
00:19:40.081 --> 00:19:43.651
N-Not this --
I'm -- I'm too stupid. Morty.

352
00:19:43.685 --> 00:19:45.086
Stupid Ted.

353
00:19:45.119 --> 00:19:47.387
If I were just
a little bit smarter. I could --

354
00:19:47.421 --> 00:19:49.123
I-I could figure it out.

355
00:19:49.157 --> 00:19:50.357
And be happy.

356
00:19:50.390 --> 00:19:51.859
I'm gonna push the button.
Morty.

357
00:19:51.893 --> 00:19:53.460
I'm -- I'm gonna do it
for you.

358
00:19:53.493 --> 00:19:56.798
Uh. if that makes you
feel better?

359
00:19:56.831 --> 00:19:58.066
Is he...

360
00:19:58.099 --> 00:19:59.667
Is he better at this?

361
00:19:59.701 --> 00:20:02.302
Rick? Um. yeah.

362
00:20:02.335 --> 00:20:04.371
Yeah. he is. <i>You</i> are.

363
00:20:04.404 --> 00:20:06.473
D-Don't --
Don't bullshit me. Morty.

364
00:20:06.507 --> 00:20:09.744
No. you're really smart.
really important.

365
00:20:09.777 --> 00:20:13.815
You have a great family.
and -- and lots of friends.

366
00:20:13.848 --> 00:20:16.316
You're...so happy.

367
00:20:16.349 --> 00:20:18.586
And...we all
really love you.

368
00:20:18.619 --> 00:20:20.988
Aw. fuck it.

369
00:20:29.130 --> 00:20:31.833
It -- It didn't work?

370
00:20:31.866 --> 00:20:33.167
No.

371
00:20:33.201 --> 00:20:35.636
It did.

372
00:20:47.280 --> 00:20:51.251
♪ I get stuck on pages ♪

373
00:20:53.487 --> 00:20:56.758
♪ You keep trying to turn ♪

374
00:20:57.925 --> 00:21:03.396
♪ Feels like I've been
on this one for ages ♪

375
00:21:05.633 --> 00:21:10.738
♪ When will I ever learn? ♪

376
00:21:10.772 --> 00:21:15.843
♪ Oooh ♪

377
00:21:17.410 --> 00:21:20.715
We've always known you as
a tourist on our little island.

378
00:21:20.748 --> 00:21:23.751
But now we're gonna
know you as part of our family.

379
00:21:23.785 --> 00:21:26.053
I love you. Sallpock.

380
00:21:26.087 --> 00:21:27.555
Mush-mush-molock.

381
00:21:27.588 --> 00:21:29.824
I didn't think
I was the kind of man --

382
00:21:29.857 --> 00:21:32.193
Sorry.
I. um --

383
00:21:32.226 --> 00:21:34.962
We love you. Sallpock!

384
00:21:34.996 --> 00:21:40.367
Should anyone object. speak now
or forever hold your peace.

385
00:21:40.400 --> 00:21:42.770
Yeah. I object.

386
00:21:42.804 --> 00:21:44.972
Shouldn't we let it play out?
He's not in danger.

387
00:21:45.006 --> 00:21:46.874
I've never seen
these people before in my life.

388
00:21:46.908 --> 00:21:50.178
Okay. Grandpa Rick. Let's go.
Vacation's over.

389
00:21:50.211 --> 00:21:52.647
It's not my vacation!
It's my home!

390
00:21:54.248 --> 00:21:56.717
No. no! Let me go! No!

391
00:21:56.751 --> 00:21:58.085
Boom. Egged!

392
00:21:58.119 --> 00:21:59.352
It's okay.

393
00:21:59.386 --> 00:22:01.289
He's an alien
who removes his intelligence

394
00:22:01.321 --> 00:22:02.489
to hook up with locals.

395
00:22:02.523 --> 00:22:03.925
He likes that you're simple.

396
00:22:03.958 --> 00:22:05.827
He doesn't want to be known.

397
00:22:06.961 --> 00:22:08.830
Did you get any of that?

